                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="3r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Epistles of Paul with preface</title>
                                <incipit>PRimum queritur quare...</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">...Salutant uos de italia gratia cum omnibus uobis amen</explicit>
                                <note>The preface on <locus from="3r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/> consists of three different parts and seems to correspond to <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107105">Stegmüller</title>
                                        <citedRange from="1" to="1" unit="volume"/>
                                        <citedRange from="290" to="291" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2r" to="122Ar" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Commentary on the Epistles</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="2ra" to="2vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Extracts from De Penitentia Salomonis, Augustine's De nuptiis et concupiscentia, and scattered Bible glosses</title>
                                    <incipit>Salomon inquit uir tante sapientie</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">que per adam intrauit in mundum hoc qui non credit infelis est.</explicit>
                                    <note>The first paragraph on 2r appears to be a version of De Penitentia Salomonis (for more on this text see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107193">DiTommaso (2017)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="371" to="452" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>), followed by Augustine's De nuptiis et concupiscentia, 1:10. After this follows what appears to be Bible glosses. On 2v the glosses are mainly on Romans.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="3r" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Commentary on the preface</title>
                                    <incipit>Si dicitur mors maledicta nemo horret</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">aut quolibet denique liniamenta natiua corrumpente medicamine.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="10r" to="28r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="uniform">Commentary on Romans</title>
                                    <incipit>Prima ponitur quia primum gradum erroris scilicet superbiam destruit</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Cui si auferas cui absoluta est lectio beatus augustinus dicit apponi et tractus quomodo debet accipi</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="28v" to="49r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on First Corinthians </title>
                                    <incipit>Chorinthi sunt achaici Hii ab ipso paulo conuersi sunt</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Maranatha magus sirum est quam ebreum tamen etsi ex confinio utrarumque linguarum aliquid et hebreum sonet et interpretatur deus noster uenit.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="49r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Second Corinthians</title>
                                    <incipit>Quibusdam chorintiorum per primam epistulam correctis</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Spiritus communis patri et filio uel ita spiritus sit uobiscum ut comunicet et conferat uobis gratiam christi et caritatem dei quod est sit tota trinitas uobiscum dans gratias de commissis et caritatem per spiritum.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="63r" to="70v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Galatians</title>
                                    <incipit>Galathe sunt greci hii ab apostolo ueritatem acceperant</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">stigmata punctum nota.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="70v" to="77v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Ephesians</title>
                                    <incipit>Ephesi sunt asiani hi per paulum confirmati in fide</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Ad similitudinem sponse que non admittit corruptionem.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="77v" to="82v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Philippians</title>
                                    <incipit>Philipenses sunt macedones hi paulo per epaphroditum aliquam substantiam romam miserant</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Impleat desiderium non in terrenis sed in gloria uel gloria christi implere desideria suorum</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="82v" to="87v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Colossians</title>
                                    <incipit>Colosenses sunt asiani quibus non ipse apostolus predicauit sed eius discipuli archippus et epaphras</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Prepositum eorum per eos commonet ut qui regendam ecclesiam eorum accepit sit sollicitus de eis plebis autem causa scribitur epistula et ideo non ad rectorem destinatur.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="88v" to="93r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on First Thessalonians</title>
                                    <incipit>Thessalonicenses sunt macedones qui facile ab apostolo conuersi</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Sancto non simulato.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="93r" to="95r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Second Thessalonians</title>
                                    <incipit>Orta grauiori tribulatione item monet patientiam ostendens iustum dei iudicium</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Vel per epistulam nostram hoc notate nobis.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="95v" to="100v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on First Timothy</title>
                                    <incipit>
                                        <sic>IEPX</sic> Timotheus iste fuit filius mulieris fidelis patre gentili </incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Prophanas ut an potasis<!--error for hypostasis?--> que uox se habet ad personam et ad substantiam</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="100v" to="103v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Second Timothy</title>
                                    <incipit>Paulus iam a mundo transiturus item scribit a roma timotheo</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Leonis quicum non patet a rusticia remouere uel de uita uult tollere ne aliis prodesset quodque non potest insultat ei apostolo.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="103v" to="105r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Titus</title>
                                    <incipit>Tyto relicto crete episcopo ex simplicitate et humilitate nimis pacienti</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">sollicite id est necessaria secum adducant.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="105r" to="105v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Philemon</title>
                                    <incipit>Philomeni familiares litteras misit pro onesimo seruo eius</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Minus exigo quam debes.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="106r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">on Hebrews</title>
                                    <incipit>Ecclesiis hebreorum scribit apostolus de eminentia christi.</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">In hoc reddit attentos.</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="122r" to="122Ar" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Freestanding commentary</title>
                                    <incipit>Calix Quia tota humana natura et in anima et corpore erit corrupta</incipit>
                                    <explicit defective="unknown">Hac autem causa factum uidetur ut scilicet inicio nascentis ecclesie nouis causis existentibus premuniret et ut presentia atque oriencia resecaret uicia</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1" to="1" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="123r" to="124v" scheme="folios"/> appear to be the old pastedown and endpaper.</p>
                                    <p> Besides the commentary in the margin the main text is also interspersed with interlinear glosses written by the same hand. <locus from="122" to="122" scheme="folios"/> is only half as wide as the other leaves.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="122A" to="122A" scheme="folios"/> consists of a small piece of parchment attached to the quire. 122Ar contains the end of the commentary, 122Av contains an addition by a later hand.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="124v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="295" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="205" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="124" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <foliation>Chapter title in red in top outer corners and chapter numbers in red Roman numerals in outer margins. </foliation>
                                    <condition>Small holes in the parchment here and there without loss of text, except for on <locus from="49" to="49" scheme="folios"/> where text has been lost.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="1" ruledLines="23">
                                        <locus from="3r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="215" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="90" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Main text: Ruling and guidelines in hardpoint. Pricking in margin.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                    <layout columns="2" ruledLines="46">
                                        <locus from="3r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written"/>
                                        <note>Commentary: The commentary is an intergral part of the page layout with its own guidelines and ruling. When the commentary is at its largest it completley surrounds the main text and has been written on hardpoint ruled lines (two lines for each line of the main text). Leaves with less commentary on them have not always been ruled in this way.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="2r" to="105v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic. </handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="106r" to="122Ar" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Upper part of page in faded ink of uncertain date: <quote xml:lang="fr">Ca livre Est de leglise ? de sainct legier du chast- a/et lodun Legier</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A poem in French written by a late-medieval hand in dark ink. The poem is 7 lines long and signed <quote xml:lang="la">Johannis</quote> + an illegible surname. The poem is repeated two more times below, but without signature. The page also contains some doodles and additional lines of text.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="63r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Short note by the same or similar hand as the the rest of the text written vertically in the outer margin.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="87v" to="87v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Several lines of glosses have been erased on the middle of the page. The text is still faintly visible.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="122Av" to="122Av" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Note by later medieval hand, 5 lines of text: <quote xml:lang="la">O uos causidici...ordo supernus</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="123r" to="124r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Notes and scribblings by one or more late-medieval hand in dark ink. Notes both in Latin and French. A note at the bottom of <locus from="123v" to="123v" scheme="folios"/> again states that the book belonged to the chapel of Saint Légier.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink, capitals in red or touched with red, rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10r" to="105r" scheme="folios"/>: zoomorph P over 8-11 lines. Every new book is introduced by a complex zoomorph P (in Paulus). These letters are outlined in ink and coloured. Main colours: red, blue, green, and yellow. In some cases, e.g. <locus from="70v" to="70v" scheme="folios"/>, only blue and red are used. The motives are zoomorph (mainly dragons) with knotwork and architectural elements (columns, acanthus), sometimes combined and sometimes isolated. Above these large initials smaller plain intials over 2-3 lines (+ extending below the line) in red or blue are usually found. These initials belong to a short introductionary paragraph. On 88v and 93r instead of the plain initials smaller versions of the zoomorph initials are used. <locus from="106r" to="106r" scheme="folios"/>: zoomorph M over 4 lines. Same style of motif and colours as the larger initials. <locus from="7r" to="103v" scheme="folios"/>: Plain initials over 1-3
                                        lines (+ extending above and below the line) in red. <locus from="3r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: Missing initials. Guide letters in lead, possibly by a later hand.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
